      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mastectomy Bill Is Sent to Governor</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>HARTFORD</dateline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Connecticut Gov John Rowland is expected to sign bill mandating 48-hour minimum hospital stay for women who undergo mastectomies (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The General Assembly sent a bill yesterday requiring a 48-hour minimum hospital stay for women who have mastectomies to Gov. John G. Rowland, who is expected to sign it.</p>
        <p>House members unanimously adopted the bill, while expressing outrage that it was even necessary to adopt legislation ''body part by body part.''</p>
        <p>The bill, already passed by the Senate, allows doctors and patients to determine whether a woman should spend 48 hours in the hospital. Connecticut's new managed care law, passed this session, gives doctors the right to ask for a longer hospital stay and gives patients the right to appeal medical decisions made by managed care companies. Legislators said they hoped that law would end the need for bills like this one.</p>
      </block>
